                {
                  "type": "frame",
                  "id": "IEklf",
                  "name": "mainContent",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "layout": "vertical",
                  "gap": 28,
                  "padding": [
                    32,
                    48
                  ],
                  "children": [
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "jgH2p",
                      "name": "h1Wrapper",
                      "gap": 10,
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "Uj22Y",
                          "name": "h1_1",
                          "fill": "#2D1F14",
                          "content": "Why Crucis",
                          "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                          "fontSize": 33,
                          "fontWeight": "700",
                          "letterSpacing": -0.33
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "tiYIq",
                      "name": "timeBadge",
                      "fill": "#EDE0CC",
                      "cornerRadius": 12,
                      "gap": 6,
                      "padding": [
                        4,
                        12
                      ],
                      "alignItems": "center",
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "icon_font",
                          "id": "gOeUo",
                          "name": "ic1",
                          "width": 14,
                          "height": 14,
                          "iconFontFamily": "Material Symbols Rounded",
                          "fill": "#785E48"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "2Snaz",
                          "name": "tx1",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "content": "~3 min read",
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 12,
                          "fontWeight": "500"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "text",
                      "id": "Gfeg6",
                      "name": "introP",
                      "fill": "#785E48",
                      "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "content": "Most AI code generators lack feedback loops. They produce code that looks right but breaks in production. Crucis closes the gap by generating adversarially-hardened test suites before writing a single line of implementation.",
                      "lineHeight": 1.6,
                      "fontFamily": "Inter",
                      "fontSize": 14,
                      "fontWeight": "normal"
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "jaRyk",
                      "name": "sectionProblem",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "gap": 12,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "fl8lu",
                          "name": "h2_prob",
                          "fill": "#2D1F14",
                          "content": "The problem",
                          "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                          "fontSize": 23,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "DVAF6",
                          "name": "probIntro",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Code generation agents can produce impressive first drafts, but they can't iterate reliably on their own. Without structured feedback, they:",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "frame",
                          "id": "Vb1yK",
                          "name": "bulletList",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "layout": "vertical",
                          "gap": 6,
                          "padding": [
                            0,
                            0,
                            0,
                            16
                          ],
                          "children": [
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "cSw30",
                              "name": "b1",
                              "fill": "#785E48",
                              "content": "•  Hardcode known inputs — the function returns 3 when it sees (1, 2) rather than actually adding",
                              "lineHeight": 1.6,
                              "fontFamily": "Inter",
                              "fontSize": 14,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "3PEZm",
                              "name": "b2",
                              "fill": "#785E48",
                              "content": "•  Miss edge cases — works for positive integers, crashes on zero or negatives",
                              "lineHeight": 1.6,
                              "fontFamily": "Inter",
                              "fontSize": 14,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "2u7bY",
                              "name": "b3",
                              "fill": "#785E48",
                              "content": "•  Satisfy tests without real logic — a lookup table that maps known inputs to expected outputs",
                              "lineHeight": 1.6,
                              "fontFamily": "Inter",
                              "fontSize": 14,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            },
                            {
                              "type": "text",
                              "id": "aiKBd",
                              "name": "b4",
                              "fill": "#785E48",
                              "content": "•  Stall without direction — when code fails, the agent needs specific, actionable feedback to make progress",
                              "lineHeight": 1.6,
                              "fontFamily": "Inter",
                              "fontSize": 14,
                              "fontWeight": "normal"
                            }
                          ]
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "hlwky",
                          "name": "closingPara",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "The core issue isn't just false-passing code — it's that agents need structured feedback loops to work autonomously. Every human checkpoint (\"did the tests catch cheating?\", \"does this generalize?\", \"does this meet style requirements?\") is a place where an agent stalls or drifts without intervention.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "type": "frame",
                      "id": "uAnak",
                      "name": "sectionSolution",
                      "width": "fill_container",
                      "layout": "vertical",
                      "gap": 12,
                      "children": [
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "MnjrF",
                          "name": "h2_sol",
                          "fill": "#2D1F14",
                          "content": "The solution: an autonomy scaffold",
                          "fontFamily": "Space Grotesk",
                          "fontSize": 23,
                          "fontWeight": "600"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "DZBto",
                          "name": "solPara",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Crucis is an autonomy scaffold for code-generating agents. It provides structured automated feedback — tests, adversarial review, constraints, holdout verification — so agents can iterate longer without human intervention. Each verification layer maps to a human checkpoint that Crucis automates.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "l5GTj",
                          "name": "tdPara",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Test-driven generation is the forcing function: tests are generated and hardened before any implementation exists. The implementation agent only sees the tests — never the objective — so it must write general code to pass them.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "Gb0mA",
                          "name": "transPara",
                          "fill": "#785E48",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "Four automated interventions replace human checkpoints:",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 14,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        },
